WEBVTT


00:00:33.688 --> 00:00:35.938
Okay. Thanks for waiting.

00:00:36.813 --> 00:00:38.313
Thank you very much.

00:00:43.605 --> 00:00:48.355
Barley shochu really hits the spot
after a visit to the detention center.

00:00:48.438 --> 00:00:51.771
Attorney Kujo,
you ignored my advice, didn't you?

00:00:52.813 --> 00:00:54.813
Do you mean about the yakuza case?

00:00:54.896 --> 00:00:56.271
On Mr. Kyogoku's orders,

00:00:56.355 --> 00:00:59.188
you went to visit the boss
of Fushimi-gumi, didn't you?

00:01:00.605 --> 00:01:04.146
If I don't take the case,
he won't get a fair defense.

00:01:04.230 --> 00:01:06.521
What do you mean by "fair defense"?

00:01:08.813 --> 00:01:11.396
It looks like
we won't see eye to eye on this.

00:01:12.438 --> 00:01:15.980
I'm simply saying this
because I'm worried about you.

00:01:17.896 --> 00:01:20.688
If you keep this up,
you won't just lose your badge.

00:01:22.313 --> 00:01:24.146
I'll end up behind bars.

00:01:24.646 --> 00:01:27.230
They'll do anything to protect themselves.

00:01:29.188 --> 00:01:33.021
-So you're worried about my life.
-You'll lose what matters most.

00:01:36.396 --> 00:01:37.813
It's not too late.

00:01:37.896 --> 00:01:40.021
I'll say it as many times as it takes.

00:01:41.313 --> 00:01:43.563
I'm worried about you, Attorney Kujo.

00:01:47.105 --> 00:01:49.980
Mr. Horikawa was sentenced to death today.

00:01:50.646 --> 00:01:54.480
Mr. Horikawa? Do you mean the case
that you were removed from?

00:01:54.980 --> 00:01:55.813
Yes.

00:01:57.438 --> 00:01:59.896
I wanted to see it through to the end.

00:02:02.438 --> 00:02:04.730
I thought it had nothing to do with me,

00:02:05.646 --> 00:02:08.188
but it's not easy to come to terms with.

00:02:22.896 --> 00:02:24.730
Excuse me. Two more, please.

00:02:24.813 --> 00:02:25.730
Got it.

00:02:27.396 --> 00:02:29.105
Thank you very much.

00:02:30.146 --> 00:02:33.605
I love reading
this column of yours, Ms. Ichida.

00:02:33.688 --> 00:02:34.688
I'm glad to hear it.

00:02:36.355 --> 00:02:39.396
Oh, and about that favor I asked…

00:02:39.480 --> 00:02:43.063
You want to interview those trying
to reintegrate into society, right?

00:02:43.146 --> 00:02:43.980
Yes.

00:02:44.605 --> 00:02:45.730
I understand.

00:02:45.813 --> 00:02:48.230
I'd be happy to help.

00:02:48.313 --> 00:02:49.730
Thank you very much.

00:02:49.813 --> 00:02:50.813
No problem.

00:02:51.521 --> 00:02:54.521
I don't know if I should ask,

00:02:54.605 --> 00:02:57.146
but why did you start this column?

00:02:59.188 --> 00:03:02.480
I used to be a reporter
for a weekly magazine.

00:03:02.563 --> 00:03:04.605
I joined a publishing company,

00:03:04.688 --> 00:03:07.688
and as a new employee,
I was assigned to the weekly magazine.

00:03:08.355 --> 00:03:12.146
Then one day, there was
an indiscriminate murder case.

00:03:12.230 --> 00:03:14.146
An indiscriminate murder?

00:03:14.230 --> 00:03:18.021
Twenty years ago, a middle-aged man
was killed on a bullet train

00:03:18.105 --> 00:03:24.230
while trying to protect another victim.

00:03:24.730 --> 00:03:26.313
Oh, that incident.

00:03:26.396 --> 00:03:29.938
At first, it was reported
as a heroic tale of an elite businessman

00:03:30.021 --> 00:03:32.938
and University of Tokyo law graduate
who saved a life.

00:03:33.021 --> 00:03:34.021
HERO STOPS A MURDER

00:03:34.105 --> 00:03:37.771
But after we published the article,
the editor in chief issued an order.

00:03:38.771 --> 00:03:41.146
"Look into the hero's
relationships with women

00:03:41.230 --> 00:03:44.313
and pick up some gossip."

00:03:44.396 --> 00:03:46.396
A FAMILY MAN
DEEP IN TRANSACTIONAL DATING

00:03:46.480 --> 00:03:48.271
The following week,

00:03:48.355 --> 00:03:51.480
an article exposed the businessman's
transactional dating history.

00:03:51.563 --> 00:03:52.563
FAMILY DIDN'T KNOW

00:03:52.646 --> 00:03:54.563
The weekly magazine sold like crazy.

00:03:54.646 --> 00:03:57.271
After that, public opinion of him
changed completely.

00:03:57.355 --> 00:03:59.646
The hero who saved a life

00:03:59.730 --> 00:04:03.105
became the target of slander
and relentless scrutiny.

00:04:06.730 --> 00:04:11.230
After that, I quit working for
the weekly magazine and left the company.

00:04:12.563 --> 00:04:16.146
I still regret writing that article.

00:04:17.021 --> 00:04:20.313
I'm sorry for making you remember
something so unpleasant.

00:04:20.938 --> 00:04:23.688
I've never forgotten about it.

00:04:26.313 --> 00:04:27.980
After the first article came out,

00:04:28.063 --> 00:04:31.730
I had an acquaintance at the funeral hall
who let me pose as an employee

00:04:31.813 --> 00:04:34.021
to gather information
on the victim's family.

00:04:35.813 --> 00:04:41.271
It was a quiet family funeral
with just the mother and son.

00:04:43.313 --> 00:04:47.021
The son was supporting his mother,
who fell to her knees, crying.

00:04:48.063 --> 00:04:50.938
I couldn't even talk to them.

00:04:52.230 --> 00:04:58.813
The son stayed up all night watching
the incense burn, even after he was alone.

00:04:59.646 --> 00:05:01.938
I'm sure he wanted to cry and scream.

00:05:02.438 --> 00:05:08.188
But it looked to me like he was
desperately trying to suppress his urges.

00:05:13.146 --> 00:05:17.521
We ended up drinking here after all, huh?

00:05:18.521 --> 00:05:20.938
Black Thunder
would've been lonely otherwise.

00:05:22.730 --> 00:05:24.521
This is the last time.

00:05:25.396 --> 00:05:28.063
I can't go along with you anymore,
Attorney Kujo.

00:05:29.313 --> 00:05:30.896
I understand.

00:05:31.438 --> 00:05:33.605
Attorney Kujo doesn't, does he?

00:05:33.688 --> 00:05:34.855
RINO

00:05:39.855 --> 00:05:41.480
Pick up the call already.

00:05:41.563 --> 00:05:43.313
Your daughter is waiting.

00:05:46.230 --> 00:05:48.938
I can tell it's your daughter
by the look on your face.

00:05:55.355 --> 00:05:56.605
Hello?

00:05:58.396 --> 00:05:59.355
Yeah.

00:06:01.855 --> 00:06:02.855
Yeah.

00:06:04.355 --> 00:06:05.188
That's fine.

00:06:06.771 --> 00:06:08.938
August 15th.

00:06:10.563 --> 00:06:11.605
Yeah.

00:06:14.396 --> 00:06:15.438
It's a promise.

00:06:17.605 --> 00:06:18.521
Yeah.

00:06:25.313 --> 00:06:27.063
Did you make a promise?

00:06:27.563 --> 00:06:28.605
Yes.

00:06:29.938 --> 00:06:32.313
I was forced to make one.

00:06:33.188 --> 00:06:37.605
Since I'm busy, she wanted to book me
in advance for her birthday next month.

00:06:41.771 --> 00:06:44.813
Please make sure
to keep your promise to your daughter.

00:06:45.438 --> 00:06:46.396
Okay.

00:06:51.230 --> 00:06:55.438
What is family to you, Attorney Kujo?

00:06:58.730 --> 00:07:01.021
I guess it's something
you can't escape from.

00:07:01.105 --> 00:07:02.771
"Can't escape from"?

00:07:05.730 --> 00:07:07.896
No matter how far you distance yourself,

00:07:08.688 --> 00:07:10.438
or change your last name,

00:07:11.646 --> 00:07:14.521
it clings tightly to your back
and won't come off.

00:07:15.021 --> 00:07:18.521
If you try to tear it off by force,
it will rip your own flesh.

00:07:18.605 --> 00:07:20.855
You're talking about
the Kurama family, right?

00:07:23.605 --> 00:07:26.021
But why do you hate them so much?

00:07:28.271 --> 00:07:31.021
If you trace it back,
it might be because of my name.

00:07:31.105 --> 00:07:31.938
Your name?

00:07:32.813 --> 00:07:37.271
My name is "Taiza," which is
the kanji for "human" spelled backwards.

00:07:39.188 --> 00:07:41.021
Apparently, my father named me.

00:07:42.938 --> 00:07:44.146
When I was a child,

00:07:44.230 --> 00:07:47.771
I was often teased for not having
my head screwed on straight.

00:07:49.855 --> 00:07:52.813
I thought,
"What a sinful name he gave me."

00:07:53.688 --> 00:07:55.688
I still resent him for it.

00:07:56.563 --> 00:08:00.980
When I was a child, I was also hated for
having the word "crow" in my last name.

00:08:01.063 --> 00:08:03.355
People said it was bad luck.

00:08:05.396 --> 00:08:07.146
I wonder which is worse…

00:08:08.396 --> 00:08:12.146
A backward human or a crow.

00:08:14.355 --> 00:08:17.438
Well, I wonder which…

00:08:24.855 --> 00:08:27.563
But your daughter
is not a member of the Kurama family,

00:08:28.646 --> 00:08:30.730
so please keep your promise.

00:08:33.605 --> 00:08:34.980
You're right.

00:09:22.563 --> 00:09:26.563
OUT OF THE OFFICE

00:10:18.688 --> 00:10:19.730
My back hurts.

00:10:20.313 --> 00:10:22.313
What a trashy place.

00:10:25.813 --> 00:10:26.730
Hello, hello.

00:10:27.230 --> 00:10:29.230
Wow, what a nice place.

00:10:30.188 --> 00:10:32.355
Sorry to bother you. Here's the key.

00:10:36.021 --> 00:10:38.521
It's okay. I took the local roads
all the way here.

00:10:39.896 --> 00:10:41.230
Thanks for your business.

00:10:41.313 --> 00:10:42.188
Let's go.

00:10:48.021 --> 00:10:50.021
Hey, how are we getting back?

00:10:51.563 --> 00:10:53.896
We'll take the bullet train
from Oyama Station.

00:10:54.480 --> 00:10:56.188
How are we getting to the station?

00:10:57.063 --> 00:10:59.230
It says here that it's a 39-minute walk.

00:10:59.313 --> 00:11:00.896
What the hell?

00:11:02.646 --> 00:11:05.646
Plus, transporting stolen cars
is the riskiest job,

00:11:05.730 --> 00:11:07.896
and we only get paid 30,000.

00:11:07.980 --> 00:11:09.188
That's lame.

00:11:09.688 --> 00:11:11.855
We're grunts, so it can't be helped.

00:11:12.938 --> 00:11:14.438
Grunts, huh?

00:11:16.313 --> 00:11:19.105
Sugawara's looking down on us,
that bastard!

00:11:20.230 --> 00:11:21.105
Huh?

00:11:21.896 --> 00:11:23.563
Are you dissing Mr. Sugawara?

00:11:25.230 --> 00:11:26.105
Hey.

00:11:26.855 --> 00:11:28.355
Let's rob that car dealer.

00:11:28.438 --> 00:11:29.271
Huh?

00:11:29.813 --> 00:11:31.771
I know where the safe and camera are.

00:11:31.855 --> 00:11:33.438
What are you talking about? No.

00:11:33.521 --> 00:11:35.438
We don't know who he's connected to.

00:11:35.521 --> 00:11:36.438
Hey.

00:11:38.063 --> 00:11:40.063
We'll be fine if we don't get found out.

00:11:53.855 --> 00:11:55.938
Yoo-hoo!

00:11:56.521 --> 00:11:58.855
Hey! Who are you guys? Hey! Stop it!

00:11:59.688 --> 00:12:00.896
I got it.

00:12:00.980 --> 00:12:03.480
No, please stop!

00:12:03.563 --> 00:12:05.313
Hey! Think about what you're doing.

00:12:05.396 --> 00:12:07.271
Open the safe!

00:12:07.355 --> 00:12:10.146
The safe!

00:12:13.146 --> 00:12:14.813
Piece of cake.

00:12:14.896 --> 00:12:16.896
That car dealer was in a panic.

00:12:16.980 --> 00:12:19.688
When you told me to bring
all the weapons I could find,

00:12:19.771 --> 00:12:21.230
I was really surprised.

00:12:21.313 --> 00:12:25.396
Oki, throw away those tools
on garbage collection day tomorrow.

00:12:25.480 --> 00:12:27.105
In the next town over.

00:12:27.688 --> 00:12:28.813
Got it.

00:12:29.896 --> 00:12:34.271
So shall we go to a hostess club
and have a blast with this money?

00:12:36.146 --> 00:12:37.980
Let's play a game first.

00:12:38.688 --> 00:12:39.730
A game?

00:12:43.396 --> 00:12:45.230
A trust game.

00:12:54.896 --> 00:12:56.646
We do this to each other.

00:12:57.605 --> 00:12:59.521
You can't do it without trust, right?

00:13:01.855 --> 00:13:03.355
You do it to me first.

00:13:04.980 --> 00:13:06.563
I'm a bit clumsy, so--

00:13:08.855 --> 00:13:09.688
Here I go.

00:13:37.980 --> 00:13:39.605
Does it hurt, Komatsu?

00:13:40.521 --> 00:13:42.271
The trust game begins here.

00:13:43.355 --> 00:13:46.271
As for the killing
of that Detective Arashiyama's daughter,

00:13:46.355 --> 00:13:48.813
if you hadn't snitched,
no one would've found out!

00:13:51.105 --> 00:13:53.396
How will you explain this at the hospital?

00:13:58.855 --> 00:14:01.063
How will you explain this?

00:14:01.646 --> 00:14:02.480
Hey.

00:14:02.563 --> 00:14:06.355
I-I'll say I was playing a game
of cutting off my own finger.

00:14:09.605 --> 00:14:10.896
Good.

00:14:16.480 --> 00:14:18.355
What's all this, all of a sudden?

00:14:19.771 --> 00:14:23.313
I wanted to fill this place with flowers,
like when I was a kid.

00:14:25.230 --> 00:14:26.355
I see.

00:14:30.855 --> 00:14:32.438
Did something happen?

00:14:32.980 --> 00:14:33.938
Huh?

00:14:35.230 --> 00:14:36.563
You look gloomy.

00:14:39.605 --> 00:14:42.313
I've decided to quit working
at Attorney Kujo's office.

00:14:43.480 --> 00:14:44.438
Why is that?

00:14:44.938 --> 00:14:47.771
I've learned a lot already.
I'll work somewhere else now.

00:14:47.855 --> 00:14:51.230
Have you already decided on a new office?

00:14:51.313 --> 00:14:52.230
Yes.

00:14:55.605 --> 00:14:58.855
Is the new attorney a good person?

00:15:00.146 --> 00:15:05.605
What's your standard for good or bad?

00:15:08.730 --> 00:15:10.771
Whether they can help people or not.

00:15:15.313 --> 00:15:18.521
Your dad was made out
to be a bad person after he died.

00:15:20.605 --> 00:15:22.646
A criminal killed him,

00:15:23.771 --> 00:15:26.105
and afterward,
he was killed by the public.

00:15:27.938 --> 00:15:29.188
Back then…

00:15:31.188 --> 00:15:34.230
no one helped us.

00:15:37.396 --> 00:15:39.188
So I want you to be…

00:15:42.605 --> 00:15:44.146
an attorney

00:15:45.396 --> 00:15:47.980
who helps the weak
who are suffering, Shinji.

00:15:51.230 --> 00:15:52.396
I know.

00:15:59.813 --> 00:16:02.188
I'm okay now.

00:16:02.688 --> 00:16:04.146
-Okay.
-Yeah.

00:16:06.605 --> 00:16:07.730
But…

00:16:09.730 --> 00:16:11.855
can I ask you for one thing?

00:16:11.938 --> 00:16:12.938
What is it?

00:16:14.938 --> 00:16:16.396
I want to meet Attorney Kujo.

00:16:21.105 --> 00:16:22.105
NAGARAGI LAW OFFICE

00:16:22.188 --> 00:16:25.188
Attorney Nagaragi,
I'm happy to work with you starting today.

00:16:25.271 --> 00:16:26.813
Likewise.

00:16:28.813 --> 00:16:30.813
-I ask for your cooperation.
-Likewise.

00:16:30.896 --> 00:16:34.771
We're more than glad to have you on board,
but I'm a little worried.

00:16:34.855 --> 00:16:35.896
About what?

00:16:36.730 --> 00:16:38.980
He's alone again.

00:16:39.813 --> 00:16:41.438
Attorney Kujo, that is.

00:17:09.480 --> 00:17:11.188
Long time no see, Inukai.

00:17:12.271 --> 00:17:13.396
What are you here for?

00:17:13.896 --> 00:17:17.771
That's no way to greet me. I spent
ten years in prison thanks to your orders.

00:17:19.646 --> 00:17:21.021
Wanna discuss the old days?

00:17:26.396 --> 00:17:29.313
-You didn't even visit me, did you?
-You refused to see me.

00:17:29.813 --> 00:17:33.021
You should've shown your sincerity
by visiting me multiple times!

00:17:35.980 --> 00:17:37.063
I don't care anymore.

00:17:38.063 --> 00:17:41.271
Three million isn't enough
for Arashiyama's daughter's murder.

00:17:41.771 --> 00:17:42.813
Prepare 300 million.

00:17:44.563 --> 00:17:45.480
300 million?

00:17:45.563 --> 00:17:46.646
Yeah.

00:17:46.730 --> 00:17:49.105
I found out after gathering information.

00:17:49.896 --> 00:17:52.021
Koyama, CEO of an adult video company.

00:17:52.105 --> 00:17:56.146
Arashiyama's daughter was his mistress.

00:17:56.230 --> 00:17:59.480
Kyogoku from Fushimi-gumi
ordered you to kill her to silence her.

00:17:59.563 --> 00:18:02.896
That's why you used us,
who were minors at the time.

00:18:02.980 --> 00:18:04.146
300 million is cheap!

00:18:04.230 --> 00:18:05.563
I know nothing about that.

00:18:07.730 --> 00:18:09.646
It's already in the past.

00:18:11.271 --> 00:18:13.105
It's not in the past.

00:18:29.063 --> 00:18:32.480
You know who this belongs to, right?

00:18:33.563 --> 00:18:36.688
We've got your right-hand man, Kuga.

00:18:37.896 --> 00:18:39.896
Mr. Sugawara wants to talk to you.

00:18:41.938 --> 00:18:45.730
You had him work
at Mr. Sugawara's nursing home

00:18:46.230 --> 00:18:48.688
and leak inside info
to the media, ruining him.

00:18:48.771 --> 00:18:50.730
You won't get away with this unscathed.

00:18:58.271 --> 00:18:59.896
Prepare 300 million yen.

00:19:00.396 --> 00:19:01.730
We'll wait a week.

00:19:03.688 --> 00:19:05.230
You're completely done for,

00:19:05.938 --> 00:19:07.188
Mibu.

00:19:40.521 --> 00:19:41.688
I heard that the kid

00:19:41.771 --> 00:19:45.021
who killed Mr. Koyama's mistress
is blackmailing you.

00:19:48.105 --> 00:19:50.646
I have a good ear for rumors.

00:19:51.521 --> 00:19:54.188
The kid and Sugawara
are trying to shake you down

00:19:54.271 --> 00:19:56.230
for 300 million yen, right?

00:19:56.730 --> 00:20:00.730
But if you pay them even once, it's over.

00:20:01.730 --> 00:20:05.730
They'll keep making petty complaints
and will strip you to the bone.

00:20:07.563 --> 00:20:08.813
Well, Mibu,

00:20:09.355 --> 00:20:12.230
I'll step in and handle this for you.

00:20:16.188 --> 00:20:17.230
No.

00:20:18.855 --> 00:20:21.355
I'll take care of my own mess.

00:20:27.230 --> 00:20:28.271
Is that so?

00:20:28.355 --> 00:20:29.355
Well, be careful.

00:20:29.938 --> 00:20:31.146
Thank you.

00:20:31.646 --> 00:20:32.938
Excuse me.

00:20:38.563 --> 00:20:40.938
You're the most dangerous one.

00:20:58.396 --> 00:21:00.021
Mibu's here.

00:21:08.105 --> 00:21:10.938
Mibu, did you bring the 300 million yen?

00:21:11.688 --> 00:21:12.771
Kuga,

00:21:12.855 --> 00:21:13.855
are you alive?

00:21:13.938 --> 00:21:16.313
No, I'm dead.

00:21:17.396 --> 00:21:18.480
Good.

00:21:19.021 --> 00:21:20.021
Let's go home.

00:21:20.605 --> 00:21:21.438
Okay.

00:21:21.521 --> 00:21:23.980
What are you two joking about?

00:21:24.480 --> 00:21:27.813
Hey, you're empty-handed.
Where's the money?

00:21:27.896 --> 00:21:29.563
Your yapping is so loud.

00:21:31.271 --> 00:21:32.396
I'm not paying, idiot.

00:21:33.855 --> 00:21:36.480
Are you messing with me, Mibu?

00:21:40.938 --> 00:21:44.688
You used Kuga to destroy
my nursing facility.

00:21:45.480 --> 00:21:47.813
I won't settle for 300 million yen.

00:21:47.896 --> 00:21:49.605
Give me all your assets.

00:21:51.105 --> 00:21:52.730
If you don't pay,

00:21:52.813 --> 00:21:55.188
I'll bury you both in the mountains.

00:21:55.271 --> 00:21:58.146
I don't have the money to pay you.

00:22:01.021 --> 00:22:02.438
Compensate me for the watch.

00:22:03.730 --> 00:22:06.480
Are you going to ask Mr. Kyogoku
to back you up?

00:22:06.563 --> 00:22:08.688
What can you do by yourself?

00:22:09.188 --> 00:22:10.188
Are you stupid?

00:22:11.855 --> 00:22:14.021
I'm always well-prepared,

00:22:14.771 --> 00:22:16.313
Mr. Sugawara.

00:22:17.063 --> 00:22:18.063
Huh?

00:22:20.563 --> 00:22:21.980
What the hell?

00:22:25.438 --> 00:22:26.855
Shut up.

00:22:39.730 --> 00:22:42.063
Are you okay, Kuga?

00:22:43.605 --> 00:22:46.271
I'm not… okay.

00:22:46.355 --> 00:22:47.480
You're a masochist.

00:22:47.563 --> 00:22:49.230
I'm not a masochist.

00:22:51.980 --> 00:22:52.813
Hey.

00:22:55.105 --> 00:22:56.730
Let go of me, damn it!

00:23:09.313 --> 00:23:12.021
If you're gonna kill me,
hurry up and get it over with,

00:23:12.521 --> 00:23:13.480
Mibu.

00:23:15.105 --> 00:23:17.271
What a drastic thing to say.

00:23:19.896 --> 00:23:21.521
I'm not going to kill you.

00:23:25.396 --> 00:23:26.355
Mr. Sugawara.

00:23:27.646 --> 00:23:29.688
I think highly of you.

00:23:33.355 --> 00:23:36.105
You're sharp-minded and good at business.

00:23:37.480 --> 00:23:38.563
But

00:23:40.021 --> 00:23:43.813
as we are now, we're just a bunch
of half-assed city thugs.

00:23:46.188 --> 00:23:48.855
To become more influential,

00:23:49.563 --> 00:23:51.730
I need your help, Mr. Sugawara.

00:23:54.605 --> 00:23:55.938
Join me.

00:23:58.021 --> 00:24:01.146
You've… got to be kidding me!

00:24:01.646 --> 00:24:03.730
You took ten years of my life,

00:24:03.813 --> 00:24:05.896
and you have the nerve to say that?

00:24:05.980 --> 00:24:07.855
You made the decision, you murderer!

00:24:10.396 --> 00:24:12.105
Think about it, Inukai.

00:24:13.688 --> 00:24:16.063
Don't direct your anger
at the wrong person.

00:24:19.980 --> 00:24:22.021
I'm Kyogoku's lapdog.

00:24:22.105 --> 00:24:24.896
I'm just like you,
a lapdog that does what it's told.

00:24:26.688 --> 00:24:27.980
But…

00:24:30.021 --> 00:24:32.896
I'll take off my collar
and give it back to him someday.

00:24:38.146 --> 00:24:39.605
Everyone…

00:24:41.646 --> 00:24:43.438
lend me your strength.

00:24:55.063 --> 00:24:56.938
Attorney Karasuma.

00:25:07.938 --> 00:25:09.355
Are you visiting someone?

00:25:09.438 --> 00:25:10.271
Yes.

00:25:10.355 --> 00:25:14.605
I just came back
from bringing the boss some food. Eel.

00:25:14.688 --> 00:25:15.896
Is that so?

00:25:16.396 --> 00:25:18.938
I heard you quit working
for Attorney Kujo. Why?

00:25:19.021 --> 00:25:20.438
Did you guys fight?

00:25:20.521 --> 00:25:22.105
You have a good ear for rumors.

00:25:22.188 --> 00:25:26.396
He's my guardian angel.
I know everything about Attorney Kujo.

00:25:26.480 --> 00:25:28.188
Guardian angel, huh?

00:25:28.271 --> 00:25:29.563
Your closer?

00:25:29.646 --> 00:25:31.105
Or should I say, your fixer?

00:25:32.105 --> 00:25:35.396
Are you going to take off on your own,
Attorney Karasuma?

00:25:36.605 --> 00:25:38.105
You can say whatever you want.

00:25:38.188 --> 00:25:42.521
Attorney Karasuma, you're still young,
so let me teach you something.

00:25:43.313 --> 00:25:47.396
Even if you think you've escaped,
once you've stepped in,

00:25:47.896 --> 00:25:52.230
a hand will reach up from the ground and
grab your arm when you least expect it,

00:25:52.855 --> 00:25:54.063
just like in Carrie.

00:25:54.771 --> 00:25:55.855
Carrie?

00:25:55.938 --> 00:25:58.105
De Palma's masterpiece.

00:25:58.855 --> 00:26:00.855
You'd better watch out.

00:26:00.938 --> 00:26:02.063
One day,

00:26:02.646 --> 00:26:08.105
zombies you don't even remember
will come crawling out.

00:26:14.646 --> 00:26:17.396
Your sins don't fade and disappear.

00:26:18.021 --> 00:26:20.605
They grow bigger without you noticing.

00:26:21.438 --> 00:26:23.313
Running away only makes things worse.

00:26:25.355 --> 00:26:26.813
I don't have time for this.

00:26:26.896 --> 00:26:28.313
Attorney.

00:26:32.105 --> 00:26:33.980
Look after your family.

00:26:46.271 --> 00:26:47.771
Hey, wait, wait!

00:26:47.855 --> 00:26:49.646
Hey, hey, hey! Wait!

00:26:49.730 --> 00:26:51.438
Destruction of property. Come on.

00:26:51.521 --> 00:26:53.271
Shut up, you bastard.

00:26:53.355 --> 00:26:55.313
Hey, wait a minute!

00:26:57.355 --> 00:26:59.313
What's wrong with you? Are you on meth?

00:26:59.396 --> 00:27:00.896
I'm not, you bastard.

00:27:00.980 --> 00:27:02.563
-Ow!
-Stay still!

00:27:02.646 --> 00:27:04.313
That hurts. Ow!

00:27:04.396 --> 00:27:05.646
Ouch, ow, ow…

00:27:05.730 --> 00:27:06.896
That hurts!

00:27:06.980 --> 00:27:07.813
Stay quiet.

00:27:07.896 --> 00:27:10.063
Call the police, you bastard!

00:27:17.521 --> 00:27:20.105
What's wrong? You look down.

00:27:23.646 --> 00:27:25.855
Did I run away?

00:27:26.480 --> 00:27:27.438
Huh?

00:27:28.230 --> 00:27:29.980
He told me I ran away.

00:27:30.480 --> 00:27:32.688
The yakuza who's close to Attorney Kujo.

00:27:34.563 --> 00:27:36.313
I'm aware of it.

00:27:37.146 --> 00:27:41.146
Attorney Kujo's clients have
multiple cases of fraud and extortion.

00:27:41.230 --> 00:27:42.855
There's a good chance

00:27:42.938 --> 00:27:45.563
he'll be charged as an accomplice
for helping them.

00:27:46.396 --> 00:27:48.980
If he's prosecuted and found guilty,

00:27:50.021 --> 00:27:51.980
he'll automatically lose his job.

00:27:52.605 --> 00:27:55.313
Even if he avoids prosecution,
a disciplinary complaint

00:27:55.855 --> 00:27:58.313
could still lead to disbarment,
in the worst case.

00:28:00.813 --> 00:28:03.438
I understand your concern,
Attorney Karasuma,

00:28:03.521 --> 00:28:05.646
but it's Attorney Kujo
we're talking about.

00:28:05.730 --> 00:28:09.855
I'm sure he's taking measures
to avoid getting entangled in any trouble.

00:28:09.938 --> 00:28:14.146
But if there was an ultimate prosecutor,
wouldn't Attorney Kujo get locked up?

00:28:15.105 --> 00:28:16.438
An ultimate prosecutor…

00:28:16.938 --> 00:28:18.313
Is there such a prosecutor?

00:28:20.605 --> 00:28:21.688
Who knows?

00:28:25.480 --> 00:28:27.396
Good article, Kurama.

00:28:27.480 --> 00:28:28.563
Good job.

00:28:29.271 --> 00:28:33.813
No, your formulation
of the hypothesis was brilliant.

00:28:33.896 --> 00:28:35.813
My hunch was mostly right. That's all.

00:28:35.896 --> 00:28:41.230
Ultimately, bad people
only care about their own gain.

00:28:41.313 --> 00:28:44.980
It's the logic of bad people.

00:28:45.688 --> 00:28:49.938
Even prosecutors acting like self-serving
corporate workers are on the rise.

00:28:50.563 --> 00:28:53.938
In that sense, I like your tenacity.

00:28:54.480 --> 00:28:55.980
Thank you very much.

00:28:56.063 --> 00:28:58.730
Since Ono has quit,
you're the only one I can rely on.

00:28:59.230 --> 00:29:00.563
I'm counting on you.

00:29:02.813 --> 00:29:06.855
What's Mr. Ono going to do
after he retires?

00:29:06.938 --> 00:29:09.146
I hear he'll be
a prosecutor-turned-lawyer.

00:29:10.813 --> 00:29:12.521
I don't like lawyers,

00:29:13.105 --> 00:29:14.021
especially,

00:29:14.896 --> 00:29:16.563
lawyers who protect bad people.

00:29:16.646 --> 00:29:17.896
I despise them.

00:29:19.063 --> 00:29:22.688
I'm sorry. I kept saying I'd treat you,
but I kept putting it off.

00:29:23.271 --> 00:29:24.938
This is my treat.

00:29:25.021 --> 00:29:28.396
No, it's fine.
I'll let you treat me at a better place.

00:29:29.021 --> 00:29:30.688
I won at the horse races today.

00:29:30.771 --> 00:29:33.396
I want to thank you
for introducing me to Ms. Ichida.

00:29:33.480 --> 00:29:34.646
She said she'd join us.

00:29:38.313 --> 00:29:39.896
Hmm, delicious. Good choice.

00:29:42.063 --> 00:29:44.146
Why'd you quit working for Attorney Kujo?

00:29:44.230 --> 00:29:45.188
Huh?

00:29:45.271 --> 00:29:47.063
I introduced you to him, right?

00:29:47.146 --> 00:29:50.313
And yet you quit without consulting
or even contacting me.

00:29:50.396 --> 00:29:52.855
You're not fit to be an adult,
let alone a lawyer.

00:29:53.896 --> 00:29:54.855
I'm sorry.

00:29:56.438 --> 00:29:57.688
What happened?

00:29:58.521 --> 00:30:00.396
If I stayed with Attorney Kujo,

00:30:00.480 --> 00:30:05.521
I wouldn't be able to do
what I should be doing.

00:30:06.355 --> 00:30:07.438
I see.

00:30:08.355 --> 00:30:12.563
So you know what you should be doing,
Attorney Karasuma.

00:30:13.438 --> 00:30:15.105
The same goes for you, right?

00:30:15.188 --> 00:30:16.980
Your job as a social worker…

00:30:18.938 --> 00:30:20.271
Somehow,

00:30:21.396 --> 00:30:23.521
I've been losing sight of it lately.

00:30:24.480 --> 00:30:25.938
Did something happen?

00:30:27.730 --> 00:30:32.271
You and Attorney Kujo use the law

00:30:32.771 --> 00:30:36.563
to protect the weak as attorneys, right?

00:30:37.063 --> 00:30:37.896
Well…

00:30:37.980 --> 00:30:40.146
And Ms. Ichida, the newspaper reporter,

00:30:40.771 --> 00:30:44.521
reports on the truth behind cases
and shares it with the public.

00:30:45.188 --> 00:30:47.813
She prevents recurrence
and helps protect society.

00:30:47.896 --> 00:30:48.896
You're right.

00:30:48.980 --> 00:30:50.938
So what should I protect?

00:30:51.521 --> 00:30:55.021
As a social worker, you help rehabilitate
people who committed crimes--

00:30:55.105 --> 00:30:57.938
But is that really protecting them?

00:30:58.021 --> 00:30:58.855
Yes.

00:30:58.938 --> 00:31:00.605
Wouldn't it be more protective

00:31:00.688 --> 00:31:04.938
to prevent them
from committing crimes in the first place?

00:31:05.021 --> 00:31:06.480
Well…

00:31:07.480 --> 00:31:10.021
I mean, what am I protecting?

00:31:10.105 --> 00:31:11.938
Should I protect their past?

00:31:12.021 --> 00:31:13.146
Or their future?

00:31:13.230 --> 00:31:14.355
How do you do that?

00:31:14.855 --> 00:31:17.146
What is it that only I can do?

00:31:19.646 --> 00:31:21.230
What do you really think it is?

00:31:34.230 --> 00:31:36.438
Hello, Ms. Ichida.
Do you think you can come?

00:31:36.521 --> 00:31:40.771
Ah, I'm sorry. I'm still staking out
the prosecutor… Maybe next time.

00:31:40.855 --> 00:31:42.063
Oh, sorry.

00:31:43.063 --> 00:31:44.480
What are prosecutors like?

00:31:44.563 --> 00:31:46.480
What do they protect?

00:31:47.188 --> 00:31:51.980
I guess they protect justice.

00:31:52.063 --> 00:31:53.896
Well, I have an aversion to them.

00:31:54.396 --> 00:31:55.563
Aversion?

00:31:56.063 --> 00:32:00.230
This country's prosecution system adopts
the principle of exclusive prosecution.

00:32:00.813 --> 00:32:02.188
Sorry, I don't get it.

00:32:02.271 --> 00:32:04.271
Simply put,

00:32:04.355 --> 00:32:06.105
only the prosecution has the power

00:32:06.188 --> 00:32:07.605
to prosecute criminal cases.

00:32:08.355 --> 00:32:11.480
In other words, if the prosecution
decides not to prosecute,

00:32:11.563 --> 00:32:13.230
it's the same as being acquitted.

00:32:14.063 --> 00:32:16.563
They have the authority
to decide people's fates.

00:32:17.855 --> 00:32:18.771
I see.

00:32:20.521 --> 00:32:23.063
I dislike prosecutors.

00:32:27.355 --> 00:32:29.313
Good evening, Prosecutor Kurama.

00:32:29.813 --> 00:32:33.980
Your article on the general contractors
was good. The manager was also pleased.

00:32:34.063 --> 00:32:36.313
Thanks to you, we got the scoop.

00:32:36.396 --> 00:32:37.896
Thank you very much.

00:32:37.980 --> 00:32:41.688
You write good articles
that move people's emotions.

00:32:44.146 --> 00:32:46.730
I have other good stories.
You want them, don't you?

00:32:49.355 --> 00:32:51.146
What's wrong? Don't you want them?

00:32:51.646 --> 00:32:52.980
Prosecutor Kurama.

00:32:55.688 --> 00:32:58.688
Your younger brother, Attorney Kujo,

00:32:58.771 --> 00:33:01.063
is meeting with the boss of Fushimi-gumi.

00:33:01.896 --> 00:33:05.813
He seems to be acting
as Fushimi-gumi's retained lawyer.

00:33:07.480 --> 00:33:08.771
One more thing…

00:33:09.480 --> 00:33:12.730
A former client of Attorney Kujo
who was on a suspended sentence

00:33:12.813 --> 00:33:14.188
was re-arrested for drugs.

00:33:14.271 --> 00:33:17.938
The suspect's with Detective Arashiyama
of the Organized Crime Division.

00:33:18.688 --> 00:33:20.438
Mr. Arashiyama, huh?

00:33:21.271 --> 00:33:22.605
Do you know him?

00:33:23.271 --> 00:33:24.896
We worked together years ago

00:33:24.980 --> 00:33:26.938
on a woman's dismemberment case.

00:33:27.021 --> 00:33:29.480
He's a detective who is really persistent.

00:33:30.646 --> 00:33:32.855
Did you know
that his daughter was murdered?

00:33:32.938 --> 00:33:34.188
I'm aware.

00:33:34.271 --> 00:33:36.605
He believes
that Fushimi-gumi's responsible,

00:33:36.688 --> 00:33:39.146
and he's still
relentlessly pursuing the case.

00:33:39.646 --> 00:33:42.313
Detective Arashiyama seems
to be after Attorney Kujo

00:33:42.396 --> 00:33:43.896
to take down Fushimi-gumi.

00:33:43.980 --> 00:33:46.355
I understand
Detective Arashiyama's assessment.

00:33:47.646 --> 00:33:52.021
It looks like Taiza's badge
is finally about to be taken from him.

00:33:52.521 --> 00:33:54.646
What are you planning to do now?

00:33:56.646 --> 00:33:59.146
Keep covering the story.
It'll make a good article.

00:34:00.646 --> 00:34:01.605
You

00:34:02.646 --> 00:34:05.313
write good articles

00:34:05.938 --> 00:34:07.855
that move people's emotions.

00:34:28.896 --> 00:34:29.730
What's wrong?

00:34:30.480 --> 00:34:32.980
My stupid junior got busted.

00:34:33.063 --> 00:34:34.646
Can you help me?

00:34:36.021 --> 00:34:38.480
He's a hopeless scumbag,

00:34:38.563 --> 00:34:41.646
but his father heads
a construction company I'm involved with.

00:34:41.730 --> 00:34:43.813
I have no choice but to take care of him.

00:34:45.438 --> 00:34:46.271
Could it be…

00:34:47.563 --> 00:34:50.730
He's a real idiot,
a product of an overindulgent parent.

00:34:51.980 --> 00:34:54.896
Are you going
to remain silent again, Morita?

00:34:55.646 --> 00:34:57.855
Your urine test came back positive.

00:34:57.938 --> 00:35:00.355
You can't run away from this,
so be prepared.

00:35:04.188 --> 00:35:06.855
By the way, I want to ask you something.

00:35:06.938 --> 00:35:09.813
Morita, when you caused that car accident,

00:35:09.896 --> 00:35:12.896
you stated in your testimony
that you'd lost your smartphone.

00:35:15.188 --> 00:35:16.021
Yes.

00:35:20.563 --> 00:35:23.230
You're using
a pretty old smartphone, aren't you?

00:35:23.313 --> 00:35:24.271
Huh?

00:35:25.188 --> 00:35:27.271
This is the smartphone you lost, right?

00:35:28.730 --> 00:35:30.563
I found it under my bed.

00:35:30.646 --> 00:35:31.730
Don't lie to me!

00:35:32.396 --> 00:35:34.938
You didn't give this to us
on purpose back then.

00:35:36.688 --> 00:35:38.438
It wasn't your idea, was it?

00:35:38.938 --> 00:35:41.730
Did Attorney Kujo tell you
to say you lost it?

00:35:48.396 --> 00:35:50.521
I'll reduce your sentence,

00:35:50.605 --> 00:35:53.105
so tell me everything, Morita.

00:35:57.563 --> 00:35:59.396
A prison sentence?

00:35:59.896 --> 00:36:01.355
Not a suspended sentence?

00:36:01.938 --> 00:36:03.480
Well, that seems impossible.

00:36:03.980 --> 00:36:06.438
Your urine test
came back positive for drugs.

00:36:06.521 --> 00:36:09.938
You had three pills of MDMA,
about one gram,

00:36:10.021 --> 00:36:11.605
and you caused property damage.

00:36:13.480 --> 00:36:15.188
No way…

00:36:16.646 --> 00:36:19.313
I'm going to prison?

00:36:20.188 --> 00:36:21.271
Mr. Morita,

00:36:21.355 --> 00:36:25.313
you were on a suspended sentence for
a traffic accident, and you reoffended.

00:36:30.938 --> 00:36:32.396
Just remain silent.

00:36:38.021 --> 00:36:39.021
What's the matter?

00:36:42.563 --> 00:36:44.438
How can we prove

00:36:44.521 --> 00:36:47.230
that Morita left his smartphone
at Kujo's office?

00:36:47.730 --> 00:36:49.730
We need three things…

00:36:49.813 --> 00:36:55.105
First, Morita's own statement
that Kujo told him to leave it there.

00:36:55.688 --> 00:36:58.688
We dangled a deal,
so if we press him a bit more, he'll talk.

00:36:58.771 --> 00:36:59.938
What's the second thing?

00:37:00.021 --> 00:37:02.646
A testimony
from another person of interest.

00:37:02.730 --> 00:37:06.646
If it matches Morita's statement,
it will be credible.

00:37:07.480 --> 00:37:09.813
The third thing is objective evidence.

00:37:11.146 --> 00:37:13.771
-Did you get the location data?
-Yes.

00:37:13.855 --> 00:37:16.855
And the location history
of the day Morita turned himself in?

00:37:18.105 --> 00:37:21.355
The address of Kujo Law Office
was in the location history.

00:37:21.438 --> 00:37:23.896
That means the smartphone was there.

00:37:23.980 --> 00:37:24.896
I see.

00:37:25.938 --> 00:37:28.646
That would be objective evidence.

00:37:29.230 --> 00:37:30.188
Yes.

00:37:30.271 --> 00:37:32.063
So we've got two things covered.

00:37:32.146 --> 00:37:35.105
We just need a testimony
from another person of interest.

00:37:35.188 --> 00:37:38.063
-Then we'll have all three things.
-That's right.

00:37:38.896 --> 00:37:40.938
Just one more.

00:37:41.021 --> 00:37:44.355
Then we can get Kujo convicted.

00:37:57.855 --> 00:37:59.271
This is delicious.

00:37:59.771 --> 00:38:01.105
I'm glad you like it.

00:38:01.605 --> 00:38:05.438
Oh, please eat this too,
while it's still hot.

00:38:05.521 --> 00:38:07.438
-Omurice?
-Yes.

00:38:07.521 --> 00:38:08.521
My dad loved this.

00:38:08.605 --> 00:38:11.480
-This is the Karasuma family's lucky meal.
-Thank you.

00:38:11.563 --> 00:38:12.605
You're welcome.

00:38:20.355 --> 00:38:21.480
This is good.

00:38:21.563 --> 00:38:22.771
-Really?
-Yes.

00:38:23.480 --> 00:38:26.396
I love the seasoning,
especially the ketchup-flavored rice.

00:38:27.188 --> 00:38:28.813
How do I put it…?

00:38:28.896 --> 00:38:31.230
You're very different
from what I imagined.

00:38:32.188 --> 00:38:37.021
People call you the "crooked lawyer,"
so I imagined a scary person showing up.

00:38:37.105 --> 00:38:39.938
-Mom!
-Huh? What?

00:38:40.021 --> 00:38:41.980
What's wrong? I'm complimenting him.

00:38:42.063 --> 00:38:43.813
She is complimenting me.

00:38:47.355 --> 00:38:50.896
-You're a good person, Attorney Kujo.
-Do you think so?

00:38:51.480 --> 00:38:55.146
People who eat food with such relish
can't be bad people.

00:38:57.230 --> 00:38:59.563
-Please, eat up.
-Okay.

00:38:59.646 --> 00:39:01.063
-Go ahead. Yes, yes.
-Thanks.

00:39:03.938 --> 00:39:08.855
Your dad used to make coffee for us
after dinner like this.

00:39:08.938 --> 00:39:10.813
Oh, yeah.

00:39:12.188 --> 00:39:15.105
He used to say, "Leave the coffee to me."

00:39:16.855 --> 00:39:18.021
All the time.

00:39:28.771 --> 00:39:30.021
Attorney Kujo.

00:39:30.105 --> 00:39:31.146
Yes?

00:39:32.105 --> 00:39:35.105
Ever since my husband passed away,

00:39:35.188 --> 00:39:36.605
until recently,

00:39:37.730 --> 00:39:41.980
I used to get emotionally distressed
while remembering the past.

00:39:43.771 --> 00:39:48.730
But I finally feel like

00:39:49.688 --> 00:39:52.438
I've gotten my emotions back.

00:39:54.896 --> 00:39:56.855
Even when he was young,

00:39:57.521 --> 00:40:00.355
your dad couldn't stand by
when he saw someone in need.

00:40:01.980 --> 00:40:06.521
I'm sure that's why he tried to help
the person who was being attacked,

00:40:07.021 --> 00:40:08.438
and this was the outcome.

00:40:09.771 --> 00:40:11.938
But even in his final moments…

00:40:14.313 --> 00:40:16.605
I don't think he had any regrets.

00:40:20.063 --> 00:40:22.938
Because that's the kind of life he lived.

00:40:29.646 --> 00:40:30.730
Here you go.

00:40:31.938 --> 00:40:33.313
Thank you.

00:40:33.396 --> 00:40:35.313
Thank you.

00:40:45.688 --> 00:40:46.980
It's delicious.

00:40:47.480 --> 00:40:48.855
I'm glad you like it.

00:40:53.855 --> 00:40:56.021
I'm sure your parents

00:40:57.105 --> 00:41:00.021
would have wanted to see
the great person you've become.

00:41:00.521 --> 00:41:01.688
I wonder about that.

00:41:02.188 --> 00:41:05.896
My mother wanted me
to become a prosecutor.

00:41:06.855 --> 00:41:10.230
But I wasn't as talented
as my father or older brother.

00:41:10.313 --> 00:41:13.938
I failed the bar exam repeatedly
and thought about giving up a few times.

00:41:14.813 --> 00:41:16.605
I thought that even if I gave up,

00:41:16.688 --> 00:41:19.438
I had to do what only I could do.

00:41:21.771 --> 00:41:25.063
My mother passed away
in my first year of high school.

00:41:25.938 --> 00:41:27.271
But she always told me

00:41:27.355 --> 00:41:29.480
to become someone who's helpful to others.

00:41:31.021 --> 00:41:32.771
I might be incompetent,

00:41:33.271 --> 00:41:35.230
but my mission is to help others

00:41:35.313 --> 00:41:36.771
and save people.

00:41:37.563 --> 00:41:40.438
I believe that I must see it to the end.

00:41:44.271 --> 00:41:47.605
I actually wanted to tell my mother
while she was still alive.

00:41:50.063 --> 00:41:55.063
I wanted to say, "I chose to be
an attorney instead of a prosecutor."

00:41:59.605 --> 00:42:01.313
"If that's the path you chose,

00:42:01.396 --> 00:42:03.355
I will support you with all my heart."

00:42:06.563 --> 00:42:07.563
I think

00:42:08.730 --> 00:42:11.063
that's what your mother would say.

00:42:23.271 --> 00:42:24.646
Attorney Kujo?

00:42:50.063 --> 00:42:52.563
Attorney Kujo, do you have a moment?

00:42:59.521 --> 00:43:00.521
Should I come back?

00:43:01.105 --> 00:43:02.063
No.

00:43:02.980 --> 00:43:04.105
What is it?

00:43:04.605 --> 00:43:05.688
Yes.

00:43:06.855 --> 00:43:09.021
Yes, please hold on a moment.

00:43:09.855 --> 00:43:11.021
Attorney Karasuma.

00:43:11.105 --> 00:43:11.938
Yes.

00:43:12.021 --> 00:43:14.396
It's a detective
from Honjo Police Station.

00:43:14.480 --> 00:43:15.605
Got it.

00:43:19.438 --> 00:43:22.230
Hello, this is Attorney Karasuma speaking.

00:43:22.730 --> 00:43:25.480
Hello, my name's Detective Arashiyama.

00:43:25.563 --> 00:43:30.438
I know very well this is unusual,
but I have a few questions.

00:43:32.271 --> 00:43:33.730
Mr. Karasuma,

00:43:33.813 --> 00:43:37.063
would you mind coming
to the police station?

00:43:37.605 --> 00:43:40.563
I don't like how Arashiyama
is pressuring Morita.

00:43:41.771 --> 00:43:44.688
If we put Detective Arashiyama's actions
in shogi terms,

00:43:44.771 --> 00:43:49.396
he's attacking Morita, the pawn,
to get you and me, the rook and bishop.

00:43:49.480 --> 00:43:51.563
Then he's aiming for Kyogoku, the king.

00:43:52.146 --> 00:43:55.605
If Morita, the pawn, switches sides
and is promoted, we're in trouble.

00:43:55.688 --> 00:43:58.021
But even the police
would need a lot of courage

00:43:58.105 --> 00:44:00.730
to conduct an official investigation
of a law office.

00:44:01.355 --> 00:44:03.355
They need solid evidence to take action.

00:44:05.438 --> 00:44:06.480
However,

00:44:08.021 --> 00:44:11.230
if they see
that they have a chance of winning,

00:44:12.396 --> 00:44:14.355
they'll crush us completely.

00:44:20.563 --> 00:44:21.938
Attorney Karasuma,

00:44:22.021 --> 00:44:25.563
could you take out your phone?

00:44:25.646 --> 00:44:26.521
Why?

00:44:26.605 --> 00:44:29.438
We want to ensure
you're not recording this conversation.

00:44:33.105 --> 00:44:34.188
Here you go.

00:44:38.188 --> 00:44:39.605
So what do you want?

00:44:40.105 --> 00:44:45.271
Why did you quit working
at Kujo Law Office, Attorney Karasuma?

00:44:45.355 --> 00:44:47.021
For personal reasons.

00:44:47.521 --> 00:44:50.146
Do I need to answer
this question in detail?

00:44:50.230 --> 00:44:54.563
Was it because you were fed up with
Mr. Kujo being entangled with criminals?

00:44:55.980 --> 00:44:59.980
The police sure love
to make baseless assumptions.

00:45:00.063 --> 00:45:01.313
Never mind.

00:45:02.188 --> 00:45:06.521
A while ago, you saw Morita hide his phone

00:45:06.605 --> 00:45:09.813
when he came to the office
for a consultation, right?

00:45:10.855 --> 00:45:11.855
What is this about?

00:45:11.938 --> 00:45:14.105
Morita told us.

00:45:16.271 --> 00:45:20.396
I handed over my phone
to Attorney Kujo as he instructed.

00:45:20.480 --> 00:45:21.771
That's what he said.

00:45:23.146 --> 00:45:28.480
The address for Kujo Law Office was found
in the location history of his phone

00:45:28.563 --> 00:45:31.480
on the day Morita turned himself in.

00:45:31.563 --> 00:45:33.771
That's a clear case
of evidence concealment.

00:45:33.855 --> 00:45:36.980
He came to the office,
so the address should be in the history.

00:45:37.063 --> 00:45:41.105
Mr. Karasuma, that pen is a bug, isn't it?

00:45:42.188 --> 00:45:45.688
I've seen one before, so I noticed it.

00:45:46.188 --> 00:45:48.438
You sure are well-prepared.

00:45:48.521 --> 00:45:52.230
You never know
when an unfair interrogation might happen.

00:45:54.271 --> 00:45:56.646
Did you perhaps record the conversation

00:45:56.730 --> 00:45:58.980
between Attorney Kujo and Morita too?

00:46:00.021 --> 00:46:02.313
Didn't you hear
Attorney Kujo's instructions

00:46:02.396 --> 00:46:04.313
to conceal the evidence?

00:46:05.188 --> 00:46:08.271
Surely you weren't an accomplice,
were you?

00:46:08.355 --> 00:46:11.730
No. Attorney Kujo
was just doing his job as a lawyer.

00:46:11.813 --> 00:46:13.021
Attorney Karasuma,

00:46:13.105 --> 00:46:16.938
if you try to cover for him,
you'll lose your badge too.

00:46:19.146 --> 00:46:21.396
Are you okay with that?
Won't your mom be sad?

00:46:22.396 --> 00:46:24.896
-This has nothing to do with my mother.
-Not true.

00:46:25.396 --> 00:46:28.646
If you get called a "crooked lawyer,"

00:46:28.730 --> 00:46:32.063
people will say
that you really are a family of villains.

00:46:32.146 --> 00:46:33.313
A family?

00:46:35.271 --> 00:46:36.396
What do you mean?

00:46:36.480 --> 00:46:40.438
I know about your father.

00:46:41.271 --> 00:46:46.105
I could have another article written
to remind the public.

00:46:46.188 --> 00:46:48.146
Fukami, stop it.

00:46:48.855 --> 00:46:50.688
Attorney Karasuma's family

00:46:50.771 --> 00:46:54.021
has suffered for a long time
because of that article.

00:46:55.146 --> 00:46:57.438
I'm sorry, Attorney Karasuma.

00:46:57.521 --> 00:46:58.855
He's being rude.

00:47:00.021 --> 00:47:04.938
But since we've called in a lawyer
in this manner,

00:47:05.021 --> 00:47:08.646
we're treating this investigation
with a certain degree of determination.

00:47:12.855 --> 00:47:14.771
If you give a statement,

00:47:14.855 --> 00:47:16.438
we can get to Kyogoku.

00:47:18.646 --> 00:47:21.188
You're the last piece of the puzzle.

00:47:22.813 --> 00:47:24.313
You can save the weak people

00:47:24.396 --> 00:47:26.521
who are suffering because of the bad guys.

00:47:29.730 --> 00:47:30.938
Let's end this.

00:47:38.355 --> 00:47:39.480
INUKAI

00:47:41.146 --> 00:47:42.146
I'm sorry.

00:47:45.896 --> 00:47:47.146
What is it, Inukai?

00:47:47.230 --> 00:47:49.230
At someone's request,

00:47:49.313 --> 00:47:52.313
I kidnapped and beat up a guy
who caused trouble.

00:47:52.396 --> 00:47:53.396
What should I do?

00:47:54.938 --> 00:47:56.063
Do you know him?

00:47:56.146 --> 00:47:57.771
No, not at all.

00:47:59.813 --> 00:48:02.396
I kidnapped him
out of view of the security cameras,

00:48:02.938 --> 00:48:04.438
so no one saw me.

00:48:04.938 --> 00:48:06.146
Leave him somewhere.

00:48:06.938 --> 00:48:08.188
Just in case, stay low.

00:48:08.271 --> 00:48:10.146
Yes, Mibu.

00:48:11.105 --> 00:48:13.105
Turn off your phone after you hang up.

00:48:13.771 --> 00:48:14.605
Huh?

00:48:15.188 --> 00:48:18.188
I don't want the police
to pick up the weak signals.

00:48:18.980 --> 00:48:20.146
Don't just turn it off.

00:48:20.230 --> 00:48:22.938
Remove the SIM card
and hide it somewhere else.

00:48:23.771 --> 00:48:24.980
O-Oh, okay.

00:48:25.063 --> 00:48:26.063
When things settle,

00:48:26.146 --> 00:48:28.605
turn on your phone
while driving on the highway.

00:48:28.688 --> 00:48:29.938
Understood.

00:48:32.563 --> 00:48:36.063
You and I are always getting
into trouble, aren't we?

00:48:36.146 --> 00:48:37.271
Yes.

00:48:44.688 --> 00:48:45.521
Excuse me.

00:48:52.105 --> 00:48:52.938
Yes?

00:48:53.021 --> 00:48:54.730
Hey, Mibu.

00:48:54.813 --> 00:48:56.688
My wife contacted me.

00:48:57.188 --> 00:48:59.938
She said our son is missing.
Do you know anything?

00:49:00.021 --> 00:49:04.438
We've tried reaching him since last night,
but I don't think it's anything serious.

00:49:08.730 --> 00:49:09.980
No, nothing.

00:49:10.063 --> 00:49:11.063
I see.

00:49:11.146 --> 00:49:12.646
Tell me if you get any info.

00:49:12.730 --> 00:49:14.063
Okay.

00:49:24.896 --> 00:49:26.271
The person you are trying…

00:49:26.355 --> 00:49:30.271
Damn it! Inukai turned off
his phone right away.

00:49:38.105 --> 00:49:39.980
Hello? What is it?

00:49:40.063 --> 00:49:42.480
Kuga, we have a problem. Find Inukai.

00:49:42.980 --> 00:49:45.146
I wanna know who
the person he kidnapped is.

00:49:49.355 --> 00:49:50.563
What do we do with him?

00:49:51.146 --> 00:49:53.105
We'll dump him at a hospital.

00:49:53.605 --> 00:49:56.480
I'll stay low just in case.
You guys should do the same.

00:49:57.188 --> 00:50:00.146
We kidnapped him without knowing much,
but what did he do?

00:50:00.646 --> 00:50:02.063
I was just asked to do this.

00:50:02.146 --> 00:50:05.438
Apparently, he's been getting cocky
and causing trouble,

00:50:05.521 --> 00:50:08.896
so I was asked to teach him a lesson.

00:50:10.688 --> 00:50:12.771
Oh?

00:50:16.896 --> 00:50:18.938
He heard our conversation.

00:50:24.813 --> 00:50:25.980
TAKESHI KYOGOKU

00:50:31.521 --> 00:50:34.563
He has an annoying face,
just like his father.

00:50:43.021 --> 00:50:44.605
Change of plans.

00:50:48.730 --> 00:50:50.771
Attorney Kujo, I'm heading back.

00:50:50.855 --> 00:50:53.771
I was about to go see Mr. Morita anyway.

00:50:55.563 --> 00:50:57.771
I'm grateful to you, Attorney Kujo.

00:50:58.605 --> 00:51:01.146
Other attorneys
have their positions to consider,

00:51:01.230 --> 00:51:02.396
so they play it safe.

00:51:03.480 --> 00:51:09.688
But you're a rare attorney
who fights for your clients.

00:51:20.563 --> 00:51:24.063
Was everything okay after my last visit?

00:51:25.688 --> 00:51:26.521
Huh?

00:51:26.605 --> 00:51:28.938
Are you still remaining silent?

00:51:36.105 --> 00:51:37.188
Um…

00:51:41.105 --> 00:51:41.938
Yes?

00:51:44.021 --> 00:51:47.730
Can I change attorneys?

00:51:50.480 --> 00:51:56.271
Well, my dad is going
to introduce me to another attorney.

00:52:28.646 --> 00:52:31.313
Relieved of duty? That's rough.

00:52:36.230 --> 00:52:39.396
Oh, right. Attorney Karasuma just left.

00:52:41.438 --> 00:52:42.521
Attorney Karasuma?

00:52:43.105 --> 00:52:45.855
We were asking him a lot of questions…

00:52:47.855 --> 00:52:49.063
about Morita.

00:53:01.521 --> 00:53:02.813
Attorney Karasuma.

00:53:04.521 --> 00:53:05.438
Attorney Kujo.

00:53:07.855 --> 00:53:08.855
Are you okay?

00:53:14.271 --> 00:53:17.646
I have a favor to ask of you,
Attorney Kujo.

00:53:19.563 --> 00:53:20.563
What is it?

00:53:22.355 --> 00:53:25.021
I want to drink coffee made by you.

00:53:29.355 --> 00:53:31.146
Thank you.

00:53:45.855 --> 00:53:48.396
You were questioned
by Detective Arashiyama

00:53:48.480 --> 00:53:49.855
about Morita's case, right?

00:53:50.855 --> 00:53:51.813
Yes.

00:53:53.105 --> 00:53:54.521
Are you okay?

00:53:56.146 --> 00:53:59.146
Don't worry. I didn't say anything.

00:53:59.646 --> 00:54:00.771
No,

00:54:01.313 --> 00:54:03.480
I'm worried about you, Attorney Karasuma.

00:54:03.563 --> 00:54:06.771
Don't worry about me.
You should worry about yourself.

00:54:08.563 --> 00:54:11.730
Detective Arashiyama
is no longer selective about his methods.

00:54:11.813 --> 00:54:15.146
To prove the truth
behind his daughter's murder,

00:54:15.230 --> 00:54:17.230
he's targeting Mibu and Kyogoku.

00:54:17.730 --> 00:54:20.063
And you're also one of his targets.

00:54:20.980 --> 00:54:22.188
I'm aware of that.

00:54:27.688 --> 00:54:29.480
He has objective evidence.

00:54:32.605 --> 00:54:34.813
I was dismissed as Morita's lawyer.

00:54:39.313 --> 00:54:41.938
He'll probably make a statement.

00:54:42.480 --> 00:54:43.938
What are you going to do?

00:54:45.855 --> 00:54:49.605
I'll just do what I have to do.

00:54:50.438 --> 00:54:53.396
Is protecting anti-social people
like Mibu and Kyogoku

00:54:53.480 --> 00:54:55.646
something you have to do?

00:54:57.563 --> 00:55:00.105
It's my duty as a lawyer.

00:55:01.313 --> 00:55:03.688
As a result, you'll be cornered.

00:55:04.188 --> 00:55:07.646
People betray others easily
to protect themselves, like Morita did.

00:55:09.188 --> 00:55:11.396
It's dangerous to get close
to your clients.

00:55:11.480 --> 00:55:13.188
You have to protect yourself.

00:55:13.271 --> 00:55:14.355
Attorney Karasuma.

00:55:16.188 --> 00:55:17.938
This city may look free.

00:55:18.021 --> 00:55:19.021
BICYCLES PROHIBITED

00:55:19.105 --> 00:55:20.230
But it's bound

00:55:20.896 --> 00:55:23.813
by regulations, rules, and laws.

00:55:23.896 --> 00:55:24.896
DON'T TEXT AND WALK

00:55:24.980 --> 00:55:28.230
There are invisible laws
in our daily lives.

00:55:30.271 --> 00:55:32.521
I believe that the law is the one thing

00:55:33.021 --> 00:55:35.355
that treats everyone equally.

00:55:35.438 --> 00:55:38.271
I'm not asking about the law.

00:55:38.355 --> 00:55:39.938
I'm asking about your emotions.

00:55:41.563 --> 00:55:42.771
My emotions?

00:55:42.855 --> 00:55:46.813
After my father was killed,
my mother was slandered by the public,

00:55:46.896 --> 00:55:49.313
so she's lived her life
suppressing her emotions.

00:55:50.146 --> 00:55:51.646
You're just like her.

00:55:52.355 --> 00:55:55.230
Your eyes look like my mother's
when she was suffering.

00:55:57.230 --> 00:55:59.063
The public will hate you even more,

00:55:59.146 --> 00:56:00.688
and you could lose your place.

00:56:00.771 --> 00:56:02.896
Can you still go on without breaking down?

00:56:06.813 --> 00:56:08.813
Honestly…

00:56:13.355 --> 00:56:14.813
I'm scared.

00:56:16.063 --> 00:56:17.355
Very scared.

00:56:19.771 --> 00:56:22.521
Before I'm a lawyer, I'm a human being.

00:56:24.271 --> 00:56:26.438
I may be a "backward human…"

00:56:28.438 --> 00:56:30.396
but I'm also a weak human.

00:56:41.730 --> 00:56:46.355
When I first took on a case
for an anti-social person as a lawyer,

00:56:47.271 --> 00:56:48.813
I was conflicted.

00:56:50.980 --> 00:56:53.980
I wondered if what I was doing
was really the right thing.

00:56:57.896 --> 00:57:03.980
But if I didn't take on the case,
someone else would have to defend them.

00:57:05.521 --> 00:57:09.271
The same goes for people oppressed
by society because they don't have money.

00:57:11.105 --> 00:57:16.230
Most lawyers don't want
to take on cases for those weak people.

00:57:19.146 --> 00:57:21.105
I learned that from experience.

00:57:23.188 --> 00:57:25.438
The law can protect human rights,

00:57:26.188 --> 00:57:28.521
but it can't protect people's lives.

00:57:29.521 --> 00:57:32.980
I wanted to protect the lives of the weak.

00:57:33.605 --> 00:57:38.271
But to do that, I had to step into the
ecosystem where the strong prey on them,

00:57:38.355 --> 00:57:40.896
the world with the bad guys
who threaten them.

00:57:44.396 --> 00:57:47.063
When a lawyer saves someone,

00:57:47.563 --> 00:57:49.521
they bring sorrow to another.

00:57:51.688 --> 00:57:53.688
So I decided

00:57:54.896 --> 00:57:56.938
to carry the weight of that sin.

00:57:57.521 --> 00:58:01.230
But if you lose your badge, you won't
be able to be a lawyer anymore.

00:58:01.730 --> 00:58:03.396
Even with the noblest intentions,

00:58:03.480 --> 00:58:05.646
you won't be able
to protect anyone anymore.

00:58:06.230 --> 00:58:08.146
You might even lose your life.

00:58:11.105 --> 00:58:13.938
I don't want you to die, Attorney Kujo.

00:58:17.105 --> 00:58:19.105
I want you to remain a lawyer.

00:58:24.063 --> 00:58:25.646
Attorney Karasuma.

00:58:28.563 --> 00:58:30.271
Thank you.

00:58:33.396 --> 00:58:36.980
Like how your mother
talked about your father…

00:58:37.980 --> 00:58:40.146
A person's way of life is revealed

00:58:40.896 --> 00:58:43.271
in the moment of their death.

00:58:45.313 --> 00:58:47.146
The way a person dies

00:58:48.563 --> 00:58:50.480
shows their way of life.

00:58:52.563 --> 00:58:55.271
Even if I lose my badge
and die as a lawyer,

00:58:56.230 --> 00:58:59.105
this is the way of life that I chose.

00:59:00.521 --> 00:59:03.146
And this is something only I can do.

00:59:04.938 --> 00:59:05.938
So,

00:59:07.230 --> 00:59:09.146
I'm prepared

00:59:10.605 --> 00:59:12.313
for whatever awaits me.

00:59:23.771 --> 00:59:25.688
Chop him up and carry him in this box.

00:59:29.230 --> 00:59:30.438
Wait a minute!

00:59:31.188 --> 00:59:33.105
My dad is Kiyoshi Kyogoku,

00:59:33.188 --> 00:59:34.896
the underboss of Fushimi-gumi!

00:59:35.396 --> 00:59:37.355
You're crossing the point of no return!

00:59:37.438 --> 00:59:38.980
Is that so?

00:59:40.521 --> 00:59:42.480
All the more reason to silence you.

00:59:46.271 --> 00:59:49.980
Boss, no one around here
saw Takeshi yesterday.

00:59:50.480 --> 00:59:52.146
Just keep looking!

00:59:52.646 --> 00:59:54.271
I have a bad feeling about this.

00:59:54.980 --> 00:59:56.563
My hunch is usually right.

00:59:56.646 --> 00:59:57.813
Stop!

00:59:59.188 --> 01:00:00.605
Stop!

01:00:02.105 --> 01:00:02.938
Mibu!

01:00:04.271 --> 01:00:07.605
Someone named Yamamoto
knows where Inukai's hideout is.

01:00:08.105 --> 01:00:10.563
-Kyogoku can't beat us there. Get in.
-Yes, sir.

01:00:15.563 --> 01:00:17.438
Any shitty information will do.

01:00:17.521 --> 01:00:19.230
Find out where Takeshi went.

01:00:19.313 --> 01:00:21.271
Find him no matter what!

01:00:23.938 --> 01:00:25.730
Please stop already!

01:00:36.771 --> 01:00:38.855
This is the last question.

01:00:39.355 --> 01:00:40.480
Okay.

01:00:41.521 --> 01:00:43.646
Right now…

01:00:46.438 --> 01:00:48.063
do you need me, Attorney Kujo?

01:00:54.646 --> 01:00:55.855
I…

01:00:58.438 --> 01:00:59.521
don't need you.

01:01:03.813 --> 01:01:05.188
Understood.

01:01:40.063 --> 01:01:41.938
Attorney Taiza Kujo.

01:01:43.938 --> 01:01:45.605
It was only for a short time…

01:01:47.605 --> 01:01:49.146
but thank you for everything.

01:01:51.646 --> 01:01:52.688
Thank you very much.

01:02:00.605 --> 01:02:01.938
Excuse me.

01:07:13.521 --> 01:07:18.521
Subtitle translation by: Miho Kunisawa